ot%3Bentrepreneurial%20gene.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EPolish%20Prime%20Minister%20Donald%20Tusk%20took%20a%20leaf%20out%20of%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20book%20last%20month%2C%20turning%20to%20a%20controversial%20entrepreneur%20for%20support%20as%20he%20pushed%20for%20deregulation%20to%20help%20boost%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresenting%20his%20government's%20economic%20plan%20in%20February%2C%20Tusk%20hailed%20%26quot%3Bthe%20moment%20when%20we%20can%20overtake%20everyone.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20light%20is%20visible%20from%20Poland%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BA%20breakthrough%20year%20means%20investment%2C%20investment%2C%20and%20yet%20more%20investment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETusk%20also%20took%20the%20opportunity%20to%20announce%20measures%20to%20deregulate%20the%20economy%2C%20calling%20on%20the%20eccentric%20Polish%20businessman%20Rafa%C5%82%20Brzoska%20to%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDo%20you%20accept%3F%26quot%3B%20Tusk%20publicly%20asked%20the%20billionaire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrzoska%20%E2%80%94%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20parcel%20locker%20business%20InPost%2C%20and%20one%20of%20Poland's%20richest%20people%20%E2%80%94%20accepted%20Tusk's%20challenge%2C%20emphasizing%20that%20he%20had%20no%20political%20aspirations%20but%20that%20he%20intended%20to%20present%20300%20recommendations%20by%20June%201.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPoland%20is%20already%20one%20of%20the%20fastest-growing%20economies%20in%20Europe.%20Some%20experts%20say%20exports%2C%20consumer%20behavior%2C%20and%20a%20well-trained%2C%20flexible%20labor%20force%20are%20the%20key%20drivers%20behind%20its%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20others%2C%20however%2C%20it's%20the%20Polish%20%26quot%3Bentrepreneurial%20gene.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rafa%C5%82%20Brzoska.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67cad5aa69253ccddf9890ed%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERafa%C5%82%20Brzoska.%3Cp%3EMateusz%20Wlodarczyk%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229d8c3cde-42b5-45ed-8192-06cfcdeae605%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EEntrepreneurship%20in%20Poland%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bentrepreneurial%20gene%26quot%3B%20was%20on%20full%20display%20in%202024%2C%20with%20more%20than%20353%2C000%20new%20businesses%20launched%20in%20Poland.%20The%20country%20is%20also%20one%20of%20Europe's%20hardest-working%20nations%20based%20on%20average%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fec.europa.eu%2Feurostat%2Fweb%2Fproducts-eurostat-news%2Fw%2Fddn-20230920-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehours%20worked%20per%20week%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPolish%20workers%20are%20%26quot%3Babove%20all%2C%20hard-working%2C%20well-educated%20and%20highly%20qualified%2C%26quot%3B%20Krzysztof%20Inglot%2C%20a%20labor%20market%20expert%2C%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20they%20often%20rise%20quickly%20through%20company%20ranks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20this%20had%20a%20lot%20to%20do%20with%20what%20he%20called%20the%20%26quot%3Bentrepreneurial%20gene%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20he%20said%20had%20been%20carved%20out%20under%20the%20years%20of%20communist%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20jokingly%20say%20that%20Poles%20are%20entrepreneurial%2C%20that%20construction%20workers%20will%20always%20try%20to%20find%20an%20easier%20solution%20to%20a%20situation.%20This%20is%20what%20makes%20us%20different%20from%20other%20nations%2C%20who%20often%20work%20according%20to%20standardized%20and%20identical%20rules.%20In%20contrast%2C%20we%20still%20have%20this%20tendency%20to%20look%20for%20alternative%20solutions%20and%20simplifications%2C%26quot%3B%20Inglot%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarcin%20Wojew%C3%B3dka%2C%20an%20expert%20in%20labor%20law%20and%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Pension%20Institute%2C%20agreed%2C%20saying%20Poles%20could%20%26quot%3Bmove%20mountains%26quot%3B%20when%20motivated%20and%20able%20to%20see%20the%20%26quot%3Bquick%20effects%20of%20our%20actions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20about%20the%20proverbial%20Polish%20plumber%20in%20Western%20Europe%2C%20but%20precisely%20about%20courage%20and%20the%20willingness%20to%20take%20risks%20if%20the%20reward%20is%20attractive%20enough.%20Poles%2C%20perhaps%20due%20to%20the%20historical%20experience%20of%20our%20ancestors%2C%20are%20able%20to%20grit%20their%20teeth%2C%20focus%20on%20the%20task%20at%20hand%2C%20and%20often%20even%20take%20shortcuts%20to%20achieve%20the%20desired%20result%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20such%20entrepreneur%20is%20Kamil%20Hagemajer%2C%20who%20runs%20a%20chain%20of%20milk%20bars%20in%20Warsaw%2C%20the%20Polish%20capital%2C%20and%20Wroclaw%2C%20in%20western%20Poland.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKnown%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bbar%20mleczny%26quot%3B%20in%20Polish%2C%20a%20milk%20bar%20is%20a%20low-cost%20caf%C3%A9%20that%20dates%20back%20to%20the%20communist%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20currently%20have%2020%20bars%20and%20employ%20about%20200%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Hagemajer%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20believed%20the%20entrepreneurial%20gene%20was%20the%20Poles'%20%26quot%3Bdominant%20trait.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20could%20see%20it%20in%20the%20communist%20years%20when%20the%20first%20businesses%20were%20born%20in%20markets%20or%20when%20people%20took%20small%20cars%20to%20transport%20sweaters%20or%20jeans%20from%20other%20countries%20and%20sell%20them%20in%20Poland%20as%20there%20were%20no%20such%20products%20in%20our%20country.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELooking%20ahead%2C%20Hagemajer%20said%20Polish%20business%20owners%20were%20ready%20to%20embrace%20modern%20technology%20to%20work%20more%20efficiently%20but%20that%20they%20still%20faced%20administrative%20and%20tax%20obstacles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20means%20that%20we%20have%20to%20rely%20on%20the%20knowledge%20of%20external%20companies%2C%20which%20often%20means%20that%20we%20lose%20authority%20over%20our%20businesses%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224740e677-7c68-48e2-a954-7d1a345b3e3a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EPoland's%20economy%20is%20growing%20despite%20issues%20faced%20by%20its%20neighbors%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20some%20forecasts%2C%20Poland's%20GDP%20growth%20will%20hit%203.5%25%20this%20year%2C%20up%20from%202.9%25%20in%202024.%20By%20comparison%2C%20the%20German%20economy%20is%20expected%20to%20grow%20by%200.2%25%20this%20year%20%E2%80%94%20according%20to%20a%20January%20forecast%20from%20the%20German%20Central%20Bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPoland%20is%20developing%20faster%20than%20Western%20European%20countries%2C%20and%20we%20can%20count%20on%20one%20hand%20the%20years%20when%20this%20was%20not%20the%20case.%20For%20various%20reasons%2C%20it%20is%20easier%20for%20less%20developed%20countries%20to%20grow%20quickly%20and%20thus%20catch%20up%20in%20terms%20of%20their%20development%2C%26quot%3B%20Piotr%20Bartkiewicz%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20Bank%20Pekao%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20large%20part%20of%20the%20German%20economy%20has%20been%20focused%20on%20the%20production%20of%20traditional%20combustion-engine%20vehicles.%20But%20strong%20competition%20from%20China%20and%20other%20countries%20has%20led%20to%20a%20slump%20in%20car%20sales.%20High%20taxes%2C%20bureaucracy%2C%20and%20rapidly%20rising%20labor%20costs%20have%20compounded%20the%20issue%2C%20with%20the%20German%20economy%20not%20seeing%20significant%20growth%20in%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20issues%20have%20potential%20knock-on%20effects%20for%20Poland.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGermany%20is%20our%20largest%20trading%20partner%2C%20accounting%20for%2027%25%20of%20Polish%20exports.%20Exports%20to%20the%20next%20countries%20on%20the%20list%20are%20over%20four%20times%20less.%20Therefore%2C%20German%20stagnation%20is%20a%20serious%20problem%20for%20exporters%2C%20even%20if%20they%20increase%20their%20market%20share%20in%20other%20countries%20and%20look%20for%20new%20sales%20markets%2C%26quot%3B%20Grzegorz%20Ogonek%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20Santander%20Bank%20Polska%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPoland%20is%20also%20facing%20the%20potential%20impacts%20of%20an%20aging%20population%20%E2%80%94%20something%20the%20country's%20Minister%20for%20Senior%20Policy%2C%20Marzena%20Ok%C5%82a-Drewnowicz%2C%20said%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Ba%20great%20challenge%26quot%3B%20moving%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20need%20to%20be%20open%20to%20new%20technologies.%20The%20labor%20resources%20in%20Poland%20are%20steadily%20shrinking%2C%20despite%20an%20influx%20of%20immigrants%2C%20which%20does%20not%20help%20economic%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20Ogonek%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2280c14e59-b59b-4523-af42-87574f640814%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E3%20reasons%20the%20Polish%20economy%20is%20growing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20such%20headwinds%2C%20the%20Polish%20economy%20has%20kept%20growing%2C%20with%20economists%20pointing%20to%20three%20key%20driving%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirstly%2C%20Polish%20exporters%20are%20finding%20new%20niches%20in%20foreign%20markets%20and%20are%20competitive%20despite%20increasing%20labor%20costs%20and%20the%20strengthening%20of%20the%20Polish%20zloty%20(PLN).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20EU%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20the%20largest%20market%20for%20Poland%2C%20but%20not%20the%20only%20one.%20In%20the%20macroeconomic%20data%2C%20we%20see%20an%20increase%20in%20exports%20to%20other%20markets%2C%20such%20as%20Asia%2C%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20or%20North%20America.%20Polish%20exports%20are%20also%20diversified%20and%20cover%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20products%2C%20including%20food%20products%2C%26quot%3B%20Bartkiewicz%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPolish%20consumers%20were%20also%20less%20affected%20by%20the%20energy%20crisis%20and%20increased%20inflation.%20Despite%20relatively%20high%20inflation%2C%20the%20decline%20in%20real%20household%20income%20in%20Poland%20was%20one%20of%20the%20smallest%20in%20the%20EU%20due%20to%20fiscal%20stimulation%20and%20high%20wage%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20there%20was%20a%20moderate%20decline%20in%20private%20consumer%20spending%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20faster%20return%20to%20growth%20and%20more%20regular%20consumer%20patterns%20%E2%80%94%20a%20process%20that%20is%20only%20just%20beginning%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThirdly%2C%20relatively%20high%20public%20investments%20(financed%2C%20among%20other%20sources%2C%20by%20EU%20funds)%20have%20been%20an%20additional%20catalyst.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20last%20factor%20will%20be%20crucial%20in%202025%2C%26quot%3B%20Bartkiewicz%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20this%20balance%20between%20exports%2C%20domestic%20consumption%2C%20and%20investments%20financed%20by%20EU%20funds%20that%20seems%20to%20be%20allowing%20the%20Polish%20economy%20to%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRegardless%20of%20what%20is%20happening%20in%20the%20global%20economy%2C%20one%20branch%20of%20our%20economy%20is%20always%20working%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Marcin%20Klucznik%2C%20senior%20advisor%20in%20the%20global%20economy%20team%20at%20the%20Polish%20Economic%20Institute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fa-new-economic-power-is-emerging-in-europe-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1741960936000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67bf4cedb8b41a9673f90b08%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fa-new-economic-power-is-emerging-in-europe-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Poland's%20economy%20has%20continued%20to%20grow%20despite%20issues%20faced%20by%20its%20neighbors.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22justyna.wecek%40fakt.pl%20(Justyna%20%C5%81ukawska)%22%2C%22enga