check%20feel%20symbolic%20of%20what%20that%20time%20felt%20like%20%E2%80%94%20complete%20chaos%2C%20no%20money%2C%20and%20making%20it%20through%20in%20ways%20that%20sometimes%20felt%20totally%20random.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223d2c1f5e-49fd-406d-a8b4-03e0307a18ca%5C%22%3EI%20graduated%20from%20college%20and%20a%20week%20later%20gave%20birth%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202008%2C%20I%20graduated%20from%20college%20with%20my%20Bachelor's%20degree%20on%20May%2010%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-interview-job-hospital-bed-after-giving-birth-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edelivered%20my%20daughter%20exactly%20a%20week%20later%3C%2Fa%3E.%20My%20husband%20still%20had%20a%20year%20of%20school%20left%2C%20so%20I%20became%20the%20sole%20supporter%20of%20our%20new%20little%20family.%20I'll%20be%20honest%20with%20you%3A%20neither%20of%20us%20had%20any%20idea%20that%20the%20US%20was%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20what%20would%20later%20be%20called%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalreservehistory.org%2Fessays%2Fgreat-recession-and-its-aftermath%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Great%20Recession%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20become%20adults%20%E2%80%94%20and%20parents%20%E2%80%94%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20a%20nationwide%20economic%20disaster%2C%20but%20for%20us%2C%20it%20was%20just%20normal%20life.%20Because%20we%20had%20gone%20straight%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmcdonalds-mcchicken-helped-postpartum-depression-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeing%20broke%20college%20students%20to%20broke%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20age%20of%20barely%2022%2C%20the%20recession%20didn't%20even%20really%20impact%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20rented%20our%20housing%20and%20spent%20no%20money%20on%20entertainment%2C%20eating%20out%2C%20or%20even%20clothing.%20We%20used%20rabbit%20ears%20on%20the%20TV%20and%20lived%20very%20simply.%20I%20worked%20the%20night%20shift%20while%20my%20husband%20was%20home%20with%20our%20daughter%2C%20and%20then%20we%20switched%20during%20the%20day%20while%20he%20went%20to%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202010%2C%20we%20welcomed%20a%20second%20daughter%20and%20bought%20our%20first%20home.%20Back%20then%2C%20because%20of%20the%20recession%2C%20there%20were%20several%20incentives%20for%20first-time%20homeowners.%20For%20instance%2C%20we%20qualified%20for%20a%20loan%20that%20required%200%25%20down%2C%20and%20we%20received%20an%20%24%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.irs.gov%2Fpub%2Firs-news%2Ffs-10-06.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E8%2C000%20tax%20credit%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20following%20year%20on%20our%20tax%20return.%20The%20cost%20of%20our%20mortgage%20was%20nearly%20the%20same%20as%20renting%2C%20and%20the%20house%20was%20near%20our%20jobs%2C%20so%20it%20made%20sense.%20And%2C%20of%20course%2C%20there's%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20purchase%20price%20of%20homes%20was%20ridiculously%20low%2C%20especially%20compared%20to%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f516b5dd-0e19-4ca1-8f15-283b2dbdce35%5C%22%3EWe%20learned%20not%20to%20expect%20anything%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThings%20weren't%20all%20peachy%20keen%2C%20though%20%E2%80%94%20my%20husband%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmom-of-five-cant-afford-paying-college-kids-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egraduated%20with%20a%20teaching%20degree%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20although%20it's%20hard%20to%20imagine%2C%20teaching%20was%20an%20incredibly%20in-demand%20job%20because%20of%20the%20recession.%20Every%20position%20he%20applied%20for%20had%20hundreds%20of%20applicants%2C%20and%20he%20was%20laid%20off%20constantly.%20We%20saw%20more%20pink%20slips%20in%20our%20first%20years%20of%20marriage%20than%20some%20people%20will%20see%20in%20a%20lifetime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20learned%20very%20quickly%20not%20to%20expect%20anything%20that%20older%20generations%20might%20have%20had.