al%20and%20moral%20issues.%20Because%20all%20three%20places%20are%20poor%2C%20and%20in%20some%20cases%20wracked%20by%20violence%2C%20the%20proposal%20also%20casts%20doubt%20on%20Trump's%20stated%20goal%20of%20resettling%20Gaza's%20Palestinians%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bbeautiful%20area.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOfficials%20from%20Sudan%20said%20they%20have%20rejected%20overtures%20from%20the%20US%2C%20while%20officials%20from%20Somalia%20and%20Somaliland%20told%20The%20Associated%20Press%20that%20they%20were%20not%20aware%20of%20any%20contacts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20Trump's%20plan%2C%20Gaza's%20more%20than%202%20million%20people%20would%20be%20permanently%20sent%20elsewhere.%20He%20has%20proposed%20the%20US%20would%20take%20ownership%20of%20the%20territory%2C%20oversee%20a%20lengthy%20cleanup%20process%20and%20develop%20it%20as%20a%20real%20estate%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20of%20a%20mass%20transfer%20of%20Palestinians%20was%20once%20considered%20a%20fantasy%20of%20Israel's%20ultranationalist%20fringe.%20But%20since%20Trump%20presented%20the%20idea%20at%20a%20White%20House%20meeting%20last%20month%2C%20Israeli%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20has%20hailed%20it%20as%20a%20%26quot%3B%20bold%20vision.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPalestinians%20in%20Gaza%20have%20rejected%20the%20proposal%20and%20dismiss%20Israeli%20claims%20that%20the%20departures%20would%20be%20voluntary.%20Arab%20nations%20have%20expressed%20vehement%20opposition%20and%20offered%20an%20alternative%20reconstruction%20plan%20that%20would%20leave%20the%20Palestinians%20in%20place.%20Rights%20groups%20have%20said%20forcing%20or%20pressuring%20the%20Palestinians%20to%20leave%20could%20be%20a%20potential%20war%20crime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20White%20House%20says%20Trump%20%26quot%3Bstands%20by%20his%20vision.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20on%20condition%20of%20anonymity%20to%20discuss%20a%20secret%20diplomatic%20initiative%2C%20US%20and%20Israeli%20officials%20confirmed%20the%20contacts%20with%20Somalia%20and%20Somaliland%2C%20while%20the%20Americans%20confirmed%20Sudan%20as%20well.%20They%20said%20it%20was%20unclear%20how%20much%20progress%20the%20efforts%20made%20or%20at%20what%20level%20the%20discussions%20took%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeparate%20outreach%20from%20the%20US%20and%20Israel%20to%20the%20three%20potential%20destinations%20began%20last%20month%2C%20days%20after%20Trump%20floated%20the%20Gaza%20plan%20alongside%20Netanyahu%2C%20according%20to%20the%20US%20officials%2C%20who%20said%20that%20Israel%20was%20taking%20the%20lead%20in%20the%20discussions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael%20and%20the%20US%20have%20a%20variety%20of%20incentives%20-%20financial%2C%20diplomatic%20and%20security%20-%20to%20offer%20these%20potential%20partners.%20It%20is%20a%20formula%20that%20Trump%20used%20five%20years%20ago%20when%20he%20brokered%20the%20Abraham%20Accords%20-%20a%20series%20of%20mutually%20beneficial%20diplomatic%20accords%20between%20Israel%20and%20four%20Arab%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20declined%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20outreach%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20offices%20of%20Netanyahu%20and%20Ron%20Dermer%2C%20the%20Israeli%20Cabinet%20minister%20and%20Netanyahu%20confidant%20who%20has%20been%20leading%20Israel's%20postwar%20planning%2C%20also%20had%20no%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Finance%20Minister%20Bezalel%20Smotrich%2C%20a%20longtime%20advocate%20of%20what%20he%20calls%20%26quot%3Bvoluntary%26quot%3B%20emigration%20of%20Palestinians%2C%20said%20this%20week%20that%20Israel%20is%20working%20to%20identify%20countries%20to%20take%20in%20Palestinians.%20He%20also%20said%20Israel%20is%20preparing%20a%20%26quot%3Bvery%20large%20emigration%20department%26quot%3B%20within%20its%20Defense%20Ministry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20a%20closer%20look%20at%20the%20places%20the%20officials%20say%20have%20been%20approached.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESudan%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20North%20African%20country%20was%20among%20the%20four%20Abraham%20Accord%20nations%20that%20agreed%20to%20normalize%20diplomatic%20relations%20with%20Israel%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20the%20deal%2C%20the%20US%20removed%20Sudan%20from%20its%20list%20of%20state%20supporters%20of%20terrorism%2C%20a%20move%20that%20gave%20the%20country%20access%20to%20international%20loans%20and%20global%20legitimacy.%20But%20relations%20with%20Israel%20never%20took%20off%20as%20Sudan%20plunged%20into%20civil%20war%20between%20government%20forces%20and%20the%20RSF%20paramilitary%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20conflict%20has%20been%20marked%20by%20atrocities%2C%20including%20ethnically%20motivated%20killing%20and%20rape%2C%20according%20to%20the%20UN%20and%20rights%20groups.%20The%20International%20Criminal%20Court%20is%20investigating%20alleged%20war%20crimes%20and%20crimes%20against%20humanity%2C%20and%20then-President%20Joe%20Biden's%20administration%20in%20January%20said%20the%20RSF%20and%20its%20proxies%20were%20committing%20genocide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20and%20Israel%20would%20be%20hard-pressed%20to%20persuade%20Palestinians%20to%20leave%20Gaza%2C%20particularly%20to%20such%20a%20troubled%20country.%20But%20they%20could%20offer%20incentives%20to%20the%20Khartoum%20government%2C%20including%20debt%20relief%2C%20weapons%2C%20technology%20and%20diplomatic%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20Sudanese%20officials%2C%20speaking%20on%20condition%20of%20anonymity%20to%20discuss%20a%20sensitive%20diplomatic%20matter%2C%20confirmed%20that%20the%20Trump%20administration%20has%20approached%20the%20military-led%20government%20about%20accepting%20Palestinians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20them%20said%20the%20contacts%20began%20even%20before%20Trump's%20inauguration%20with%20offers%20of%20military%20assistance%20against%20the%20RSF%2C%20assistance%20with%20postwar%20reconstruction%20and%20other%20incentives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20officials%20said%20the%20Sudanese%20government%20rejected%20the%20idea.%20%26quot%3BThis%20suggestion%20was%20immediately%20rebuffed%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20one%20official.%20%26quot%3BNo%20one%20opened%20this%20matter%20again.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMilitary%20chief%20Gen.%20Abdel-Fattah%20Burhan%20told%20an%20Arab%20leaders'%20summit%20last%20week%20in%20Cairo%20that%20his%20country%20%26quot%3Bcategorically%20rejects%26quot%3B%20any%20plan%20that%20aims%20to%20transfer%20%26quot%3Bthe%20brotherly%20Palestinians%20from%20their%20land%20under%20whatever%20justification%20or%20name.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESomaliland%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESomaliland%2C%20a%20territory%20of%20over%203%20million%20people%20in%20the%20Horn%20of%20Africa%2C%20seceded%20from%20Somalia%20over%2030%20years%20ago%2C%20but%20it%20is%20not%20internationally%20recognized%20as%20an%20independent%20state.%20Somalia%20considers%20Somaliland%20part%20of%20its%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESomaliland's%20new%20president%2C%20Abdirahman%20Mohamed%20Abdullahi%2C%20has%20made%20international%20recognition%20a%20priority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20American%20official%20involved%20in%20the%20efforts%20confirmed%20that%20the%20US%20was%20%26quot%3Bhaving%20a%20quiet%20conversation%20with%20Somaliland%20about%20a%20range%20of%20areas%20where%20they%20can%20be%20helpful%20to%20the%20US%20in%20exchange%20for%20recognition.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20possibility%20of%20US%20recognition%20could%20provide%20an%20incentive%20for%20Abdullahi%20to%20back%20away%20from%20the%20territory's%20solidarity%20with%20the%20Palestinians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%2C%20another%20Abraham%20Accord%20country%20that%20has%20developed%20strong%20ties%20with%20Israel%2C%20once%20had%20a%20military%20base%20in%20Somaliland%20and%20maintains%20commercial%20interests%20there%2C%20including%20a%20port.%20The%20territory's%20strategic%20location%2C%20in%20the%20Gulf%20of%20Aden%20waterway%20near%20Yemen%2C%20home%20to%20the%20Houthi%20rebel%20group%2C%20could%20also%20make%20it%20a%20valuable%20ally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20years%2C%20Somaliland%20has%20been%20lauded%20for%20its%20relatively%20stable%20political%20environment%2C%20contrasting%20sharply%20with%20Somalia's%20ongoing%20struggles%20amid%20deadly%20attacks%20by%20al-Qaida-linked%20operator%20group%20al-Shabab.%20Since%201991%2C%20Somaliland%20has%20maintained%20its%20own%20government%2C%20currency%20and%20security%20structures.%20Still%2C%20it%20has%20one%20of%20the%20lowest%20income%20levels%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20official%20in%20Somaliland%2C%20speaking%20on%20condition%20of%20anonymity%20because%20he%20was%20not%20authorized%20to%20talk%20to%20the%20media%2C%20said%20his%20government%20has%20not%20been%20approached%20and%20is%20not%20in%20talks%20about%20taking%20in%20Palestinians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESomalia%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESomalia%20has%20been%20a%20vocal%20supporter%20of%20the%20Palestinians%2C%20often%20hosting%20peaceful%20protests%20on%20its%20streets%20in%20support%20of%20them.%20The%20country%20joined%20the%20recent%20Arab%20summit%20that%20rejected%20Trump's%20plan%20and%20seems%20like%20an%20unlikely%20destination%20for%20Palestinians%2C%20even%20if%20they%20did%20agree%20to%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESambu%20Chepkorir%2C%20a%20lawyer%20and%20conflict%20researcher%20in%20Nairobi%2C%20Kenya%2C%20said%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20understand%20why%20Somalia%20would%20want%20to%20host%20Palestinians%20given%20the%20country's%20strong%20support%20for%20Palestinian%20self-rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20realignments%20keep%20changing%2C%20and%20so%20maybe%20there%20is%20a%20hidden%20agenda%2C%26quot%3B%20Chepkorir%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Somali%20official%2C%20speaking%20on%20condition%20of%20anonymity%20because%20he%20was%20not%20authorized%20to%20talk%20to%20the%